SIMPLE: shrinkage
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Shrinkage
<hw>Shrink"age</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act
of shrinking; a contraction into less bulk or measurement.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The amount of such contraction; the bulk or
dimension lost by shrinking, as of grain, castings, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Decrease in value; depreciation.</def>
<mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shrinker</ent>⟦br⟧
